data.text:
Alan Keen prepared for life as an MP with a diverse career which included spells as a scout for a football club, a desk job in the Army and a period in the fire protection industry. He entered Parliament as Labour MP for Feltham & Heston in 1992 and served on the Culture, Media and Sport Select Committee as well as chairing the All-Party Parliamentary Football Group.

David Alan Keen was born in Lewisham, southeast London, in 1937 but was taken by his mother to her family home in Cleveland at three weeks.
